    Description
    Amoeba
    Represents an Amoeba entity in the game.

    BlueDoor
    Represents a locked door that can only be unlocked with a BlueKey.
    BlueKey
    Represents a BlueKey that can be used to unlock BlueDoor objects.

    Represents a Boulder item in the game.

    ControllersTestStage
    A test stage for setting up and displaying the game interface.
    Data
    A singleton class responsible for managing user data and game levels.
    Direction
    Enum representing the four cardinal directions: UP, DOWN, LEFT, and RIGHT.
    Dirt
    Represents a Dirt tile in the game.
    Enemy
    This Abstract Enemy class extends Entity and is intended to hold an abstract functions to find its future moves.
    Entity
    Abstract Entity class derived from abstract GameObject class.
    Exit
    Represents an Exit tile in the game.
    Explosion
    Represents an Explosion tile in the game.
    Firefly
    The Firefly class represents a specific type of enemy with unique movement patterns.
    Frog
    This Frog class moves towards the player using A* algorithm and kills on touch
    GameController
    GameController class is responsible for managing the core logic of the game.
    GameObject
    Abstract GameObject class that holds the sprite, centre of sprite, position, update rate and collision status of game objects.
    GameWindowController
    Controller class responsible for managing the game window, including game state, pause menu, and UI updates.
    Gem
    The Gem class represents a gem item that can be collected by the player.
    Goblin
    This Goblin class is a branch of Frog intended to steal diamonds from the player, then explode when they touch instead of killing the player.
    GraphicsController
    The GraphicsController class is responsible for rendering game objects on the provided canvas.
    GridPosition
    Represents integer position pair.
    HelloController
    handles the functionality for the initial screen of the application.
    HighScore
    The HighScore class represents a high score achieved by a user.
    Item
    The Item class represents an entity that can fall and roll in the game.
    Key
     
    KeyColour
    Enum representing the various colors of keys in the game.
    Level
    Represents a level in the game, storing high scores and providing methods to manage level data and user scores.
    LevelController
    Controller for managing the level selection and game state.
    LockedDoor
    Abstract class representing a locked door on the game map.
    MagicWall
    Represents a MagicWall tile on the game map.
    Main
    Sample application that demonstrates the use of JavaFX Canvas for a Game.
    MainUI
    Main class to launch the JungleGameStart application.
    Map
    Representation of the game's map.
    NewProfileController
    Code for NewProfile window.
    Node
    Nodes for the A* pathfinding.
    Path
    Class for Path tile.
    PathfindingEnemy
    Super for Frog and Goblin, uses A* to find the fastest path to the player.
    PatrollingEnemy
    Super for Butterfly and Firefly, uses Movement priority to find the next path to move to.
    PinkDoor
    A class representing a locked pink door in the game.
    PinkKey
    A class representing a pink key in the game.

    RedDoor
     
    RedKey
    Represents a RedKey in the game, extending from the Key class.

    Utility class for saving invalid input: '&' loading map data.

    Abstract Tile class derived from abstract GameObject class.
    TimeController
    Manages the timing and updates for the game, handling ticks and checking for game events such as player death or victory.
    TitaniumWall
    Represents an indestructible wall in the game that cannot be walked through or destroyed.

    Represents a user in the game with their name, unlocked levels, and the current level in progress.

    Controller class for the user selection screen in the application.

    Represents a wall tile in the application.

    Represents a yellow door in the application.
    YellowKey
